[Episode 10]

42
00:02:23,540 --> 00:02:26,540
Little Master, help me.

43
00:02:27,220 --> 00:02:30,180
Little Master, help me.

44
00:02:50,740 --> 00:02:51,860
That's her.

45
00:02:52,500 --> 00:02:54,020
Little Master.

46
00:02:55,220 --> 00:02:55,860
Miss Mei.

47
00:02:59,420 --> 00:03:00,300
Zuo, You.

48
00:03:13,780 --> 00:03:16,220
Little Master, help me.

49
00:03:16,860 --> 00:03:18,260
I'm here. Don't be afraid.

50
00:03:19,500 --> 00:03:20,300
Your Highness.

51
00:03:20,300 --> 00:03:21,180
Go get the Grand Tutor.

52
00:03:21,180 --> 00:03:22,260
The Grand Tutor?

53
00:03:22,260 --> 00:03:23,740
- Maybe we can find someone else.
- Quickly!

54
00:03:24,700 --> 00:03:25,900
I want the best physician.

55
00:03:28,180 --> 00:03:28,780
Yes.

56
00:03:29,900 --> 00:03:31,300
Your Highness, Miss Mei is...

57
00:03:31,300 --> 00:03:34,260
No one can know about today.

58
00:03:35,220 --> 00:03:36,700
If someone gets punished for this,

59
00:03:37,540 --> 00:03:38,540
I will not forgive you.

60
00:03:38,540 --> 00:03:39,900
But Miss Mei broke into
the Eastern Palace...

61
00:03:39,900 --> 00:03:40,860
What do you mean by breaking into?

62
00:03:42,900 --> 00:03:43,940
By my order,

63
00:03:44,580 --> 00:03:45,540
from today on,

64
00:03:45,540 --> 00:03:47,300
Miss Mei has free access
to the Eastern Palace.

65
00:03:47,900 --> 00:03:49,180
No one shall stop her.

66
00:03:50,780 --> 00:03:51,300
Yes.

67
00:03:51,300 --> 00:03:51,940
Leave us.

68
00:04:09,780 --> 00:04:11,700
It's late. Douzi is still not back yet.

69
00:04:12,460 --> 00:04:13,860
I wish nothing bad happened.

70
00:04:23,940 --> 00:04:25,220
What is going on in there?

71
00:04:25,820 --> 00:04:28,180
Nanbei and Zuo left in such a hurry.

72
00:04:28,820 --> 00:04:30,020
Something must have happened.

73
00:04:30,620 --> 00:04:31,700
Stop it.

74
00:04:31,860 --> 00:04:32,860
Mind your own business.

75
00:04:36,740 --> 00:04:37,380
Stop.

76
00:04:38,060 --> 00:04:39,180
Where are you from?

77
00:04:39,580 --> 00:04:41,460
What are you doing
away from your lady so late?

78
00:04:41,620 --> 00:04:43,020
Where are you going?

79
00:04:43,020 --> 00:04:43,740
I...

80
00:04:44,860 --> 00:04:45,460
Take her.

81
00:05:05,780 --> 00:05:06,420
Grand Tutor.

82
00:05:07,060 --> 00:05:07,660
Hurry up.

83
00:05:07,660 --> 00:05:09,100
- Who would do this to an old man?
- Hurry!

84
00:05:09,100 --> 00:05:10,300
Getting me out of the warm bed

85
00:05:10,300 --> 00:05:11,460
- in the middle of the night.
- It's a life-or-death situation.

86
00:05:11,460 --> 00:05:12,740
The Crown Prince
asked for you specifically.

87
00:05:12,740 --> 00:05:13,740
Exactly.

88
00:05:14,180 --> 00:05:15,580
So I have to come because he asked?

89
00:05:15,700 --> 00:05:17,300
- I'm going back to bed.
- Grand Tutor!

90
00:05:22,220 --> 00:05:23,900
Aren't you the servant girl
from the Family Mei?

91
00:05:24,580 --> 00:05:25,860
What are you doing here?

92
00:05:25,860 --> 00:05:27,500
I'm here waiting for you.

93
00:05:27,500 --> 00:05:29,060
Please help save lives.

94
00:05:29,100 --> 00:05:31,140
Scholars of the past told us
a man's life is worth more than gold.

95
00:05:31,180 --> 00:05:32,860
One who saves lives is worth even more.

96
00:05:32,940 --> 00:05:35,020
Grand Tutor, you are kind and skillful.

97
00:05:35,020 --> 00:05:35,860
That's why HisHighness

98
00:05:35,860 --> 00:05:37,500
insists on inviting you
to the Eastern Palace.

99
00:05:39,060 --> 00:05:40,500
You...

100
00:05:41,100 --> 00:05:43,060
You're very good with your words.

101
00:05:43,980 --> 00:05:45,700
You're trying to talk me into this.

102
00:05:46,260 --> 00:05:47,780
But I quite like it.

103
00:05:47,780 --> 00:05:48,900
I am pleased.

104
00:05:51,420 --> 00:05:56,140
You're so much better
than those at Chongwen Academy.

105
00:05:56,340 --> 00:05:57,420
Thank you.

106
00:06:01,220 --> 00:06:02,940
What are we waiting for?
Let's go save lives.

107
00:06:04,220 --> 00:06:05,020
Grand Tutor, this way.

108
00:06:07,060 --> 00:06:08,100
The Grand Tutor has arrived.

109
00:06:09,980 --> 00:06:10,900
The medical kit.

110
00:06:11,380 --> 00:06:12,140
Come here.

111
00:06:12,180 --> 00:06:12,820
This way.

112
00:06:15,540 --> 00:06:17,100
Please wait here, Miss.

113
00:06:17,140 --> 00:06:18,700
The Crown Prince won't let anyone in.

114
00:06:18,700 --> 00:06:20,300
Also, thank you for earlier.

115
00:06:27,780 --> 00:06:28,980
Princess Yueying.

116
00:06:34,500 --> 00:06:35,340
Mei?

117
00:06:36,220 --> 00:06:37,020
Xing Shi.

118
00:06:41,700 --> 00:06:43,780
Do you maybe need something?

119
00:06:44,300 --> 00:06:44,860
I...

120
00:06:46,460 --> 00:06:47,100
Miss Mei,

121
00:06:47,420 --> 00:06:48,780
I wonder if we can talk in private?

122
00:06:48,780 --> 00:06:50,340
There's no one else here.

123
00:06:50,340 --> 00:06:52,260
We can talk here.

124
00:06:54,180 --> 00:06:55,060
I'd like to ask...

125
00:06:55,340 --> 00:06:57,460
How have you been all this time?

126
00:06:58,060 --> 00:06:59,140
All this time?

127
00:07:10,420 --> 00:07:11,340
Thank you, Miss.

128
00:07:11,460 --> 00:07:12,220
Don't worry.

129
00:07:12,460 --> 00:07:13,380
I'll come back for them later.

130
00:07:15,220 --> 00:07:15,980
I think

131
00:07:16,140 --> 00:07:18,380
you look like
an old acquaintance of mine.

132
00:07:18,620 --> 00:07:20,020
Sorry if I startled you.

133
00:07:20,980 --> 00:07:21,580
My bad.

134
00:07:21,580 --> 00:07:22,300
Can you tell me

135
00:07:22,380 --> 00:07:25,100
who is the servant girl
that His Highness just carried

136
00:07:25,180 --> 00:07:26,220
into the room?

137
00:07:26,220 --> 00:07:29,060
She's not a servant girl.
She's the Grand Chancellor's daughter.

138
00:07:30,460 --> 00:07:31,220
Why did you carry these here?

139
00:07:31,220 --> 00:07:32,780
That old man is so annoying.

140
00:07:32,780 --> 00:07:34,940
He insists
on lighting a fire in the room.

141
00:07:35,020 --> 00:07:36,060
Go on then.

142
00:07:41,420 --> 00:07:42,780
Are you looking for the Crown Prince?

143
00:07:43,260 --> 00:07:43,780
I...

144
00:07:44,260 --> 00:07:44,900
How about

145
00:07:44,900 --> 00:07:46,460
I ask for
the Crown Prince's permission first

146
00:07:46,460 --> 00:07:48,220
and you wait in the side hall?

147
00:07:48,220 --> 00:07:50,180
Take a right
and then a left along this road.

148
00:07:50,180 --> 00:07:51,300
It's right at the end.

149
00:07:53,300 --> 00:07:54,180
Give me these.

150
00:07:54,980 --> 00:07:55,980
Thank you, Miss.

151
00:08:05,740 --> 00:08:06,700
Where's my lady?

152
00:08:06,780 --> 00:08:07,580
How is she?

153
00:08:08,620 --> 00:08:10,100
She needs to recover
in the Eastern Palace.

154
00:08:14,980 --> 00:08:16,260
Thank you, Your Highness.

155
00:08:16,580 --> 00:08:17,660
But I'm afraid it's improper.

156
00:08:18,020 --> 00:08:19,620
If my lady stays in the Eastern Palace,

157
00:08:19,620 --> 00:08:20,780
people will start talking.

158
00:08:21,060 --> 00:08:22,700
But she's still in a coma.

159
00:08:23,100 --> 00:08:23,980
How does she leave?

160
00:08:24,700 --> 00:08:27,140
Your Highness's reputation
is also at stake.

161
00:08:27,140 --> 00:08:29,540
Please allow me to bring my lady back.

162
00:08:56,620 --> 00:08:57,420
What are you eating?

163
00:08:58,860 --> 00:09:00,420
You scared me, young lady.

164
00:09:03,500 --> 00:09:05,180
What a waste of such a good thing!

165
00:09:05,900 --> 00:09:07,020
You're still laughing.

166
00:09:07,580 --> 00:09:08,540
Stupid girl.

167
00:09:08,620 --> 00:09:10,220
You don't understand. With some spices

168
00:09:10,220 --> 00:09:11,580
and pepper,

169
00:09:13,300 --> 00:09:14,660
it would be so good.

170
00:09:14,820 --> 00:09:16,380
Who says I don't understand?

171
00:09:16,700 --> 00:09:17,580
No, no.

172
00:09:17,580 --> 00:09:19,860
Save me some. Come on.

173
00:09:21,300 --> 00:09:22,860
You...

174
00:09:28,140 --> 00:09:30,460
You have potential.

175
00:09:31,460 --> 00:09:33,620
You're so much better
than those servant girls.

176
00:09:33,740 --> 00:09:35,180
The last time I ate this,

177
00:09:35,700 --> 00:09:36,700
they were scared,

178
00:09:36,700 --> 00:09:38,060
asking me if it was poisonous.

179
00:09:38,980 --> 00:09:40,060
Not as knowledgeable as you.

180
00:09:40,060 --> 00:09:42,940
Of course. I've eaten so many things.

181
00:09:45,300 --> 00:09:46,420
What have you eaten?

182
00:09:46,820 --> 00:09:47,500
Cicadas.

183
00:09:47,860 --> 00:09:48,660
Pupa cicadas.

184
00:09:48,900 --> 00:09:50,980
And even grasshoppers.

185
00:09:51,580 --> 00:09:53,900
These are what poor citizens eat.

186
00:09:53,900 --> 00:09:55,580
Do you also eat those wild things

187
00:09:55,580 --> 00:09:56,700
at the Grand Chancellor's Residence?

188
00:09:56,700 --> 00:09:59,100
I've also eaten snakes and toads.

189
00:09:59,100 --> 00:10:01,220
And unborn chickens.

190
00:10:02,900 --> 00:10:04,340
You also eat unborn chickens?

191
00:10:05,060 --> 00:10:06,740
Dead in the egg?

192
00:10:06,900 --> 00:10:08,580
Wide open eyes?

193
00:10:09,100 --> 00:10:11,420
They also have wings and legs.

194
00:10:11,420 --> 00:10:12,380
Roast them first.

195
00:10:12,380 --> 00:10:14,100
The taste is so much better than eggs.

196
00:10:15,740 --> 00:10:17,740
You make it sound really tasty.

197
00:10:17,740 --> 00:10:18,740
I'll have to try it sometime.

198
00:10:21,580 --> 00:10:23,060
You drink this medicine first.

199
00:10:26,860 --> 00:10:28,740
You only need one bowl of my medicine.

200
00:10:28,740 --> 00:10:30,340
I promise, within two days,

201
00:10:31,420 --> 00:10:33,860
you'll be alive and kicking.

202
00:10:34,020 --> 00:10:34,940
Really?

203
00:10:34,940 --> 00:10:35,980
I don't believe it.

204
00:10:36,580 --> 00:10:37,500
Why don't you?

205
00:10:37,780 --> 00:10:39,060
If it's not real,

206
00:10:39,060 --> 00:10:40,460
can I still be an Imperial Physician?

207
00:10:40,900 --> 00:10:43,780
I don't think teaching and medicine are

208
00:10:43,780 --> 00:10:45,100
the same thing.

209
00:10:45,100 --> 00:10:46,300
It's the same.

210
00:10:47,180 --> 00:10:48,500
Scholars in the past
have already told us

211
00:10:48,540 --> 00:10:50,820
that you can find beauty in the books

212
00:10:50,820 --> 00:10:53,020
as well as all the wealth you need.

213
00:10:53,020 --> 00:10:54,380
Different herbs together

214
00:10:54,620 --> 00:10:56,780
will produce a certain drug.

215
00:10:57,580 --> 00:10:59,580
The ancestors
have already put these things

216
00:10:59,580 --> 00:11:01,180
- in the books then.
- Grand Tutor.

217
00:11:01,180 --> 00:11:01,980
Listen to them.

218
00:11:01,980 --> 00:11:03,820
- It can't go wrong.
- Look at my situation.

219
00:11:03,820 --> 00:11:06,140
You still want to give me lessons.

220
00:11:06,300 --> 00:11:07,940
Take your medicine then.

221
00:11:12,460 --> 00:11:13,340
So bitter.

222
00:11:13,340 --> 00:11:15,340
It's killing me in my belly.

223
00:11:16,100 --> 00:11:18,420
Bitter medicine is good medicine.

224
00:11:18,620 --> 00:11:20,580
To be honest with you,
I never gave this to anyone.

225
00:11:20,580 --> 00:11:22,580
This is my deepest secret.

226
00:11:23,100 --> 00:11:25,300
I didn't even give it to the Empress.

227
00:11:26,340 --> 00:11:27,780
Fine, fine. I'll drink it all.

228
00:11:27,780 --> 00:11:28,780
Not a drop left.

229
00:11:28,940 --> 00:11:29,460
Good.

230
00:11:35,500 --> 00:11:36,420
I need to tell you.

231
00:11:37,060 --> 00:11:38,580
The Crown Prince forced me to come

232
00:11:38,580 --> 00:11:39,860
in the middle of the night.

233
00:11:41,060 --> 00:11:42,500
Baking a midnight snack by his bed,

234
00:11:42,500 --> 00:11:44,460
I must be the first
and only one in the palace.

235
00:11:46,020 --> 00:11:46,980
From today on,

236
00:11:46,980 --> 00:11:48,780
Miss Mei has free access
to the Eastern Palace.

237
00:11:49,300 --> 00:11:50,620
No one shall stop her.

238
00:11:53,740 --> 00:11:54,500
Look at you.

239
00:11:55,060 --> 00:11:56,620
What a waste this is!

240
00:11:58,660 --> 00:12:00,060
What a waste!

241
00:12:00,540 --> 00:12:01,860
You have no idea.

242
00:12:02,700 --> 00:12:03,700
With all due respect,

243
00:12:03,900 --> 00:12:05,300
she must stay here today.

244
00:12:05,500 --> 00:12:07,260
If anyone finds out
that she was wounded here,

245
00:12:07,540 --> 00:12:08,740
they will need an explanation.

246
00:12:10,780 --> 00:12:13,460
I guess I didn't think this through.

247
00:12:13,820 --> 00:12:17,020
I'd like to stay and take care of her
in the Eastern Palace.

248
00:12:20,460 --> 00:12:21,140
May as well.

249
00:12:22,300 --> 00:12:23,660
You know her needs better.

250
00:12:26,020 --> 00:12:27,300
I've been wondering

251
00:12:28,540 --> 00:12:30,380
why your lady changed so much

252
00:12:30,900 --> 00:12:33,100
after that night at the Museum.

253
00:12:33,980 --> 00:12:35,100
Did something happen

254
00:12:35,100 --> 00:12:36,060
and I don't know yet?

255
00:12:37,020 --> 00:12:38,420
What Your Highness said

256
00:12:38,900 --> 00:12:40,300
makes no sense to me.

257
00:12:41,060 --> 00:12:42,220
Mei?

258
00:12:45,100 --> 00:12:46,060
Mei.

259
00:12:50,060 --> 00:12:51,100
You woke up already.

260
00:12:51,620 --> 00:12:52,820
Looks like it was right
to get the Grand Tutor.

261
00:12:53,140 --> 00:12:54,660
I will take full responsibility.

262
00:12:55,340 --> 00:12:56,420
Did he give you a hard time?

263
00:12:56,500 --> 00:12:57,140
What?

264
00:12:59,100 --> 00:13:01,860
I mean, you're so busy.

265
00:13:01,860 --> 00:13:04,100
Why are you talking to my servant girl?

266
00:13:04,100 --> 00:13:05,780
My lady, Her Highness was...

267
00:13:05,780 --> 00:13:07,180
We were talking about secrets,
of course.

268
00:13:08,100 --> 00:13:09,140
For example,

269
00:13:10,060 --> 00:13:12,260
someone just had to hold...

270
00:13:12,260 --> 00:13:13,020
Stop.

271
00:13:13,340 --> 00:13:14,060
Hold what?

272
00:13:15,420 --> 00:13:16,900
A... A rabbit.

273
00:13:17,300 --> 00:13:19,020
